    {
      "level": "A1",
      "title": "Word order in present simple questions",
      "slug": "a1-word-order-in-present-simple-questions",
      "order": 83,
      "chapter": "Questions",
      "description": "The order of words in an English question in present simple is QWASI: (Question Word) + Auxiliary + Subject + Infinitive. What do you do? Where do they live? In Yes-No questions (questions that we answer saying yes or no) there is NO Question Word. Do you speak English? Does she live here? The auxiliary verb in present simple is be or do/does. Below, you can see a grammar chart on the order of words in present simple questions with be or do/does.",
      "analogy": "",
      "real_world_use": "",
      "memory_hook": "",
      "icon": "⏰",
      "rules": [
        {
          "title": "Questions with am/is/are",
          "formula": "When the verb in the sentence is be, we use am/is/are as the auxiliary verb before the subject. Then the word order is QWAS: (Question Word) + Auxiliary (am/is/are) + Subject",
          "explanation": "",
          "memory_hook": "",
          "is_exception": false,
          "order": 1,
          "examples": []
        },
        {
          "title": "Questions with do/does",
          "formula": "When we have a verb that is not be, we use do/does as the auxiliary verb.\nWe use does with he/she/it and do with I/you/we/they. Remember that the main verb after the subject is in the infinitive form (NOT -s or -es).",
          "explanation": "",
          "memory_hook": "",
          "is_exception": false,
          "order": 2,
          "examples": [
            {
              "sentence": "What does she do?",
              "translation": "",
              "context": "",
              "highlight": ""
            },
            {
              "sentence": "What does she does?",
              "translation": "",
              "context": "",
              "highlight": ""
            },
            {
              "sentence": "Where does he work?",
              "translation": "",
              "context": "",
              "highlight": ""
            },
            {
              "sentence": "Where does he works?",
              "translation": "",
              "context": "",
              "highlight": ""
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "level": "A1",
      "title": "Question words – Grammar chart",
      "slug": "a1-question-words-grammar-chart",
